snippet.title: ISIS is the World's Richest Terrorist Group

localized.description:
ISIS (The Islamic State in Iraq and al-Sham) is the world's richest terrorist group notably surpassing the well-known al Qaeda and Taliban organizations. This is all according to the International Business Times who called ISIS the world's richest terror force after the group captured Mosul and made off with half-a-billion-dollars from the city's central bank. The Islamic extremist group is spreading across Iraq seizing land and oil wells with the intention of establishing Sharia law in Iraqi and Syrian territories. We take a look at how ISIS was able to accumulate their enormous wealth in such a short period of time, in this Lip News clip with Elliot Hill and Mark Sovel.

http://thelip.tv/show/the-lip-news/
